	(127,'5.1.1','Ensure that anti-virus programs are capable of det...','Ensure that anti-virus programs are capable of detecting; removing; and protecting against all known types of malicious software.','NA',69,1,4,'2017-04-10 13:56:03','2017-04-10 13:56:03'),
	(128,'5.1.2','For systems considered to be not commonly affected...','For systems considered to be not commonly affected by malicious software; perform periodic evaluations to identify and evaluate evolving malware threats in order to confirm whether such systems continue to not require anti-virus software.','NA',69,1,4,'2017-04-10 13:56:03','2017-04-10 13:56:03'),
	(129,'5.2','Ensure that all anti-virus mechanisms are maintain...','Ensure that all anti-virus mechanisms are maintained as follows: • Are kept current; • Perform periodic scans • Generate audit logs which are retained per PCI DSS Requirement 10.7.','NA',69,1,4,'2017-04-10 13:56:03','2017-04-10 13:56:03'),
	(130,'5.3','Ensure that anti-virus mechanisms are actively run...','Ensure that anti-virus mechanisms are actively running and cannot be disabled or altered by users; unless specifically authorized by management on a case-by-case basis for a limited time period.Note:Anti-virus solutions may be temporarily disabled only if there is legitimate technical need; as authorized by management on a case-by-case basis. If anti-virus protection needs to be disabled for a specific purpose; it must be formally authorized. Additional security measures may also need to be implemented for the period of time during which anti-virus protection is not active.','NA',69,1,4,'2017-04-10 13:56:03','2017-04-10 13:56:03'),
